  // Mail
  "Amichwan.DinoExpanded.Mail.GuntherEggDonation": "Dear @:^^After receiving the egg you kindly donated to the museum, it was analyzed by the Academy of Sciences of the Ferngill Republic.^^The results were surprising, as despite its fossilized appearance, a weak but constant biological activity was detected inside.^^^^Unfortunately, the museum does not have suitable facilities to handle such a specimen. I have provided Robin with blueprints for a structure specially designed for its study and care.^^If you wish to continue this research, I recommend visiting her.^^Sincerely,^^Gunther ¦Dear @:^^After receiving the egg you kindly donated to the museum, it was analyzed by the Academy of Sciences of the Ferngill Republic.^^The results were surprising, as despite its fossilized appearance, a weak but constant biological activity was detected inside.^^^^Unfortunately, the museum does not have suitable facilities to handle such a specimen. I have provided Robin with blueprints for a structure specially designed for its study and care.^^If you wish to continue this research, I recommend visiting her.^^Sincerely,^^Gunther",
  "Amichwan.DinoExpanded.Mail.DemetriusDinoEgg": "Hello @,^^I was reviewing some new blueprints in Robin’s workshop, and one in particular caught my attention. When she explained what it was for, I couldn’t help but connect it to the egg you donated to the museum.^^I’ve been doing some research on my own, and all signs suggest that this egg is no ordinary fossil. If the building you constructed works as intended, I would like to ask you a favor: could you bring me an egg so I can study it more closely?^^I promise to handle it carefully and share any interesting discoveries with you.^^—Demetrius %item quest Amichwan.DinoExpanded_DinoEggQuest %%[#]Experiment Results",
  "Amichwan.DinoExpanded.Mail.DemetriusMissionComplete": "Hello @,^^Thank you for the egg. What I’ve discovered is truly remarkable. It appears that the genetic material of the Pepper Rex can be combined with other fossil remains to give rise to new forms of life.^^I’ve built a machine that allows this process, and I’ve noted down how to craft it, in case you wish to try it yourself.^^One warning, however: there are records of similar experiments that did not end well… so proceed with caution.^^—Demetrius %item craftingRecipe Amichwan.DinoExpanded_GeneticFuser %%[#]Experiment Results",
  "Amichwan.DinoExpanded.Mail.MarlonDinoGear": "Hey @,^^I’ve been experimenting with parts that some dinosaurs leave behind. As a seasoned adventurer, I recognize the value of such resilient materials.^^The scales are incredibly tough, the claws sharp as razors, and the hooves can provide an edge in mobility. If you’re interested, I have a few samples available at the Adventurer’s Guild.^^A tip that might help you: during molting, some dinosaurs can shed their scales. With the right tool, it’s possible to collect them carefully, much like with other farm animals.^^Stay safe out there,^^— Marlon",
  "Amichwan.DinoExpanded.MarlonDinoBoots": "Hey @,^^I’ve been experimenting with parts that some dinosaurs leave behind. As a seasoned adventurer, I recognize the value of such resilient materials.^^The scales, sharp claws, and hooves are incredibly tough. If you’re interested, I have a few samples available at the Adventurer’s Guild.^^A tip that might help you: during molting, some dinosaurs can shed their scales. With the right tool, it’s possible to collect them carefully, much like with other farm animals.^^Stay safe out there,^^— Marlon",
  "Amichwan.DinoExpanded.Mail.Dinoincubator": "Hello @,^^I’ve been closely following the progress you’ve made in researching and raising these ancient species.^^Based on the observations gathered, I’ve developed a specialized incubator for dinosaurs. This device fine-tunes incubation conditions to make the process more efficient, reducing the required time without affecting natural development.^^I believe this tool could be a valuable aid in continuing your studies.^^—Demetrius %item craftingRecipe Amichwan.DinoExpanded_DinoIncubator %%[#]Specialized Incubation",
